---
import AnimateOnEnter from './AnimateOnEnter';
---

<AnimateOnEnter client:visible>
  <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold leading-tight mb-8">
    Energy is a <span class="highlight">human right</span>. Shutoffs are <span class="highlight">not</span>.
  </h1>
  <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      We are the Energy Equity Project. We believe every person in this country deserves power in their home — the lights, the heat, the oxygen concentrator, the insulin fridge, the fan in August — as a matter of human right, not a matter of whether they could pay this month.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not believe shutoffs should be reduced. We believe they should be <strong><span class="highlight">abolished</span></strong>. Not reformed. Not softened with seasonal moratoriums or medical exemptions that turn into paper mazes. Abolished — the way the country once abolished other practices it had the power to end and chose to end.
    </p>
    <p>
      What follows is one year in America: 2024, as reported by utilities themselves to the federal government. It is not the whole story. It is not the worst of it. It is what the utilities admit to, in the numbers they file. Read it and decide whether another world is possible.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col items-start gap-2 text-sm text-ink/50" aria-hidden="true">
    <span>Scroll to continue</span>
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 animate-bounce" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
    </svg>
  </div>
</AnimateOnEnter>
